===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|敬|馬|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s}}, as horses are [[skittish]] (easily startled and frightened).

===Etymology 1===
Compare {{cog|okz|kreṅa||to fear}}, whence {{cog|km|ក្រែង||to fear}}, {{cog|th|เกรง||to fear; to worry}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Within Chinese, cognate with {{och-l|敬|to be respectful; to warn}}, {{och-l|警|to warn; to be on one's guard}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). A possible vocalic variant is {{zh-l|兢|to be cautious}}.

